<H3> <TI>   Qian Qichen Meets Russian Deputy Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Qian Qichen Meets Russian Deputy Foreign Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1204073394 Beijing XINHUA in English 0655 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1204073394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 12 (XINHUA) -- The series of visits 
scheduled to be exchanged between China and Russia this year 
will help further promote the relations between the two 
countries, said Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian 
Qichen . 
  Qian made the statement during his meeting with visiting 
deputy Foreign Minister Alexsandr Panov of Russia here this 
morning. 
  Qian and Panov exchanged views on bilateral relations and 
international issues of common concern. 
  Qian said that Russia is a big country that plays an 
important role in world affairs, adding that China always puts 
its relations with Russia high on its foreign policy agenda. 
  Qian said that there has been healthy and steady development 
recently in the bilateral relations, adding that the developing 
of good neighborly relations between the two countries not only 
conforms to the interests of the countries themselves, but also 
constitutes a stabilizing factor in the Asia-Pacific region and 
the world as a whole. 
  The Chinese vice-premier expressed his belief that the 
bilateral relations will be further developed though joint 
efforts. 
  Panov expressed his satisfaction over the positive results 
of 
his current visit to China. He held that Russia-China relations 
will become better and better. 
  Yesterday afternoon Chinese Deputy Foreign Minister Dai 
Bingguo held talks with Panov on bilateral relations and other 
issues of common concern. 

</TEXT>

