<H3> <TI>   Group of Hong Kong Affairs Consultants Chosen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Group of Hong Kong Affairs Consultants Chosen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1104071094 Beijing XINHUA in English 0642 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1104071094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 11 (XINHUA) -- A third group of 50 
consultants on Hong Kong affairs is to be engaged by the Hong 
Kong and Macao Affairs Office of the State Council and the Hong 
Kong branch of XINHUA NEWS AGENCY. 
  A list of the names of the 50 consultants was announced here 
today. Included are legislative members Peggy Lam and H.C. 
Cheng, Lee Guo-wei, chairman of the Hang Seng Bank Ltd., and 
Cheng Yin-chung, director of the city polytechnic college. 
  An appointment ceremony for the consultants will be held 
here 
in the middle of May. 

</TEXT>

