<H3> <TI>   Jiang Zemin Meets Washington State Governor </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Jiang Zemin Meets Washington State Governor </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1304102194 Beijing XINHUA in English 0832 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1304102194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 13 (XINHUA) -- Chinese President 
Jiang Zemin met with Washington Governor Mike Lowry and his 
party here today. 
  Extending a welcome to Lowry on his first visit to China, 
Jiang said he hoped U.S. guests could visit China more 
frequently in the future so as to gain a better understanding of 
China's reform, opening and modernization drive. 
  Previously, Jiang met with the governor in Seattle where he 
was attending an APEC meeting last November. 
  Lowry and his party came to China as guests of the 
government 
of southwest China's Sichuan Province, with which Washington has 
been a sister state since 1981. 
  During the meeting in Zhongnanhai, Jiang expressed hopes 
that 
Sichuan Province and Washington State would make greater efforts 
to push forward the cooperation links between them, and between 
the two countries as well. 
  Lowry said his visit to Sichuan was impressive and that his 
delegation is "here to learn and further strengthen cooperation 
with China." 

</TEXT>

