<H3> <TI>   U.S. Bank Opens Office in Shanghai </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Bank Opens Office in Shanghai </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1204120494 Beijing XINHUA in English 1138 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1204120494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, April 12 (XINHUA) -- The Shanghai office 
of the First National Bank of Boston, a large bank of the United 
States, was open here today. 
  This is the 64th office of foreign financial institutions 
that have opened in this commercial and financial center of 
China. 
  According to administrative regulations issued by the 
Chinese 
Government regarding foreign financial institutions, such 
offices can be upgraded into branches after two years in the 
country. 
  Local sources said the majority of the offices have plans to 
become branches. 
  Ira Stepanian, president of First National of Boston, who 
attended the opening of the bank's office. Said that his bank 
is confident in China's financial market. 
  He expressed his hope that the bank would soon set up at 
least five such offices in China, which would be soon upgraded 
into branches. 
  He disclosed that the Beijing office of this world-known 
bank 
will also be opened soon. 
  First National of Boston, founded in 1784, has over 100 
branches and offices worldwide, and it now has branches in Hong 
Kong, Taipei, Tokyo, Singapore, Seoul and Manila. 

</TEXT>

