<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Voices Opposition </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Voices Opposition </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1304033594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0142 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1304033594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Madrid, April 12 (XINHUA) -- Russian President 
Boris Yeltsin, on an official visit to Spain, voiced here today 
his opposition to the NATO air strikes against Serb positions in 
Bosnia. 
  At a press conference held after his talks with Spanish 
Prime 
Minister Felipe Gonzalez, Yeltsin said those who ordered the 
attacks will have to assume responsibility for possible 
subsequent failure of the peace plan for the area. 
  Yeltsin was angered by not being consulted on the air 
strikes 
on Sunday and Monday, asking about how Russia could enter into 
partnership with NATO when Russia is ignored constantly. 
  He said Russia has enough means and forces to impose its 
influence on the situation in former Yugoslavia and have its 
views considered in the world political arena. 
  Yeltsin arrived here Monday for a three-day visit for 
discussions with Spanish leaders on promotion of bilateral 
relations and international issues. 

</TEXT>

