  [Text] Beijing, April 12 (XINHUA) -- Premier Li Peng met a 
delegation of friendship from Tokyo, Japan's capital, led by its 
mayor Suzuki Shunichi, here this afternoon. 
  Li offered congratulations on the fact that cooperation and 
friendly exchanges have developed in all fields between Beijing 
and metropolitan Tokyo since they cemented sister-ties 15 years 
ago. 
  He also praised Suzuki's contribution to the development of 
Sino- Japanese relations, especially Beijing-Tokyo relations. 
  He said the two countries' bilateral ties have a good growth 
momentum, with busy personnel exchanges and expanded exchanges 
and cooperation in the fields of trade and economy, culture and 
education, and science and technology. 
  Li said it was worth noting that many cities in China and 
Japan have established friendly relations. 
  Suzuki and his party, who arrived here today as guests of 
the 
Beijing municipality, will take part in a series of events 
organized by Beijing to celebrate the 15th anniversary of the 
establishment of its sister-relations with Tokyo. 

