<F P=100> Near East &amp; South Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jiang Zemin Meets Nepalese Guests 13 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Jiang Zemin Meets Nepalese Guests 13 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1304102894 Beijing XINHUA in English 0930 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1304102894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 13 (XINHUA) -- Chinese President 
Jiang Zemin said here today that the varied cooperations between 
China and Nepal have been satisfactory. 
  He made the remarks at a meeting with Beni Bahaour Karki, 
chairman of the upper house of Nepal's Parliament. 
  China and Nepal are good neighbors, and the Nepalese-Chinese 
friendship has a long history, Jiang said. 
  He said that the two countries' cooperation in the fields of 
politics, culture, economy and trade in recent years is 
satisfactory. 
  Extending a welcome to Karki on his first visit to China, 
Jiang said he hoped that the guests will gain a better 
understanding of China during their stay. 
  Karki said that one of the purposes of his visit is to see 
the changes brought about by the Chinese Government's policies 
of reform and opening to the outside world. 
  He also said that the Nepalese people and government would 
never forget the aid and support China has offered for the 
economic development of Nepal. 
  Ngapoi Ngawang Jigme, vice-chairman of the National 
Committee 
of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference 
(CPPCC), was present at the meeting. 
  The Nepalese visitors arrived in Lhasa, capital of the Tibet 
Autonomous Region, April 9 to begin a ten-day visit to China as 
guests of the CPPCC National Committee. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

