<H3> <TI>   Bangladesh Foreign Minister Departs on China Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bangladesh Foreign Minister Departs on China Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1204174994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1551 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1204174994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dhaka, April 12 (XINHUA) -- Bangladesh Foreign 
Minister Mustafizur Rahman left here tonight to pay a five-day 
visit to China beginning tomorrow. 
  Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen, who 
paid a four-day visit to Bangladesh in February, extended the 
invitation. 
  Economic and trade relations between Bangladesh and China 
will get prominence at the talks between the two sides, the 
Foreign Ministry said. 
  Bangladesh is now attaching more importance to economic 
diplomacy in keeping with its overall objective of achievement 
of the national economic development. 
  During the visit, the Bangladesh foreign minister will meet 
his Chinese counterpart and other Chinese leaders to exchange 
views on further strengthening the existing cooperative and 
excellent bilateral relations between the two countries. 
  He will also discuss regional and international issues of 
common concern with the Chinese leaders, the Foreign Ministry 
said. 

</TEXT>

