<F P=103> OW1204140694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 12 (XINHUA) -- Visiting Portuguese 
Prime Minister Anibal Cavaco Silva said here today that Portugal 
and China enjoy good political relations and their cooperation 
in economy, finance and trade has a bright future. 
  Speaking at a press conference the prime minister said that 
he and Chinese leaders had discussions on bilateral ties, the 
Macao question as well as some international issues in a 
friendly atmosphere. 
  Expressing satisfaction at the implementation of the joint 
declaration on Macao, Silva said that Portugal and China will 
continue their dialogue and do their best to resolve all 
problems that may crop up during Macao's transition period with 
a view to ensuring Macao's stability, prosperity and development 
and helping its residents maintain their confidence. 
  Earlier today, Portuguese Foreign Minister Jose Durao 
Barroso 
and his Chinese counterpart Qian Qichen held talks on bilateral 
ties and international issues of common interest. 
  Prime Minister Silva and his party are scheduled to leave 
Beijing tomorrow on a tour of southern China. 

</TEXT>

