<H3> <TI>   Reportage on Portuguese Prime Minister's Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on Portuguese Prime Minister's Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Cavaco Silva on Timor, Macao </H4>

<F P=102> LD1204144194 Lisbon RDP Antena 1 Radio Network in Portuguese 
1300 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1204144194 </F>
<F P=104>  Lisbon RDP Antena 1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] This is the second day of Prime Minister Cavaco 
Silva's visit to China. He broached the question of Timor 
today. He asked the Chinese Government to contribute to a just 
solution to the problem of East Timor. He stressed that the 
Chinese contribution should come within the UN framework. 
  [Begin Cavaco Silva recording] We believe that there are two 
issues in Timor: the question of respect for human rights, which 
we will continue to advocate here and anywhere else in the 
world, and there is the question of the occupation by a foreign 
power of a territory that, according to international law, is 
still under Portuguese administration. Therefore, we are asking 
the Chinese Government for support, so that within the UN's 
framework, under the auspices of the UN secretary general, a 
just and internationally accepted solution can be found for the 
problem of Timor. [end recording] 
  As for the nationality of the Macanese, Cavaco Silva said 
that he had been informed that the Chinese authorities did not 
intend to impose Chinese nationality on the residents of Macao 
who are of Portuguese descent and culture. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

