<H3> <TI>   Shanghai Mayor Huang Ju Meets German Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shanghai Mayor Huang Ju Meets German Foreign Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1304062794 Beijing XINHUA in English 0550 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1304062794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn, April 12 (XINHUA) -- German Foreign Minister 
Klaus Kinkel told Huang Ju, the mayor of China's biggest city of 
Shanghai, here today that more German enterprises are being 
encouraged to go to Shanghai to develop economic cooperation 
with China. 
  The German minister praised China's economic achievements 
and 
opening and reform policies and those of Shanghai in particular. 
  Huang Ju briefed Kinkel on the fruitful cooperation that 
already exists between Shanghai and several German enterprises. 
  The Chinese mayor met with German Minister of Economic 
Cooperation Carl-Dieter Spranger later today and they exchanged 
views on technical, training and economic cooperation. 
  Huang Ju, who arrived in Germany on Sunday [10 April], is 
due 
to call on Chancellor Helmut Kohl on Wednesday. 

</TEXT>

