<H3> <TI>   AFP Informed of Release </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    AFP Informed of Release </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK1304075894 Hong Kong AFP in English 0746 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> HK1304075894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 13 (AFP) -- The Chinese government 
officially confirmed Wednesday that dissident Xu Wenli, detained 
last Friday in Beijing, is free. "Xu Wenli has complete freedom 
of movement," a Public Security Ministry spokesman told AFP by 
telephone. The spokesman said "Xu has been free since Saturday 
after being held legally for 24 hours." But according to 
relatives, the dissident was only released Tuesday. 
  Xu, 49, a leader of the 1978-79 Democracy Wall movement and 
one of China's longest serving political prisoners, had been 
detained as part of a police sweep of dissidents in Beijing and 
Shanghai that coincided with the visit of French Prime Minister 
Edouard Balladur. 

</TEXT>

