<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fujian's Quanzhou Implements New Tax System </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fujian's Quanzhou Implements New Tax System </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK1204071294 Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE in Chinese 0816 
GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1204071294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Shi Qingbin (2457 3237 1755)] </F>
  [Text] Quanzhou, 11 Apr (ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE)--Since the 
implementation of the new taxation system this year, various 
kinds of taxes collected by Quanzhou City have grown steadily. 
In the first two months alone, various kinds of taxes collected 
by the city reached 300 million yuan, 26.8 percent up on the 
same period last year. 
  This year is the first year in which China has implemented 
its new taxation system. It is known that in implementing the 
new taxation system, the Quanzhou City government has 
extensively publicized the new tax laws to increase 
understanding of them among people in various circles. At the 
same time, taxation departments at all levels have also 
energetically conducted special inspection, especially 
inspections of some major taxpayers whose tax payments are in 
arrears, and they have fixed time limits for tax payments. As a 
result, the new taxation system has been operating quite 
effectively. 
  At the same time, taxation departments have seriously done a 
good job in guiding taxpayers to calculate and pay value-added 
tax and other taxes. They have also taken special measures 
toward supply and marketing enterprises, materials enterprises, 
and commercial enterprises to guard against fraud. 
  Moreover, taxation departments have concentrated their 
efforts on the collection and management of various kinds of 
local taxes to prevent tax losses. 

</TEXT>

