<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Coastal Forest Belt in Shandong Described </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Coastal Forest Belt in Shandong Described </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1304042394 Beijing XINHUA in English 0234 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1304042394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jinan, April 13 (XINHUA) -- A long, winding 
ecological forest belt embracing the easternmost tip of the 
Shandong Peninsula in eastern China has taken shape through 
decades of efforts by local people. 
  The coastal green protective line is typically 100 to 2,000 
m 
wide, with trees of selected species, shrubs and grass. 
  The belt is playing a great part in preventing the loss of 
water and the erosion of soil in the coastal areas. 
  Every year millions of tourists come here to enjoy 
themselves 
in the dense woods and on the soft, sandy beaches. 
  To take advantage of the large stretches of wooded areas, 
local governments are planning varieties of forest and island 
tourist cooperative projects with foreign businessmen. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

