<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shanghai Develops Area in Western Suburbs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shanghai Develops Area in Western Suburbs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1204022994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0124 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1204022994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, April 12 (XINHUA) -- China's largest 
industrial metropolis of Shanghai has launched a program to 
develop the area in the western suburbs. 
  The area, with nearly 300 ha under the development program, 
will become another of the city's new industrial bases. 
  It is only six km from the Hongqiao International Airport 
and 
linked closely with Zhejiang, Jiangsu and Anhui Provinces. 
  Within the area, necessary key infrastructural facilities 
such as a transformer substation, a water plant and a 
program-controlled telephone system have been built. 
  So far 32 industrial projects, mainly from joint ventures 
with businessmen from Singapore, Hong Kong and Taiwan, have 
become established in the area with a total investment of more 
than 80 million U.S. dollars. 
  Among them technology-intensive and labor-intensive projects 
co-exist, as do those which are export-oriented or serving 
domestic markets. 

</TEXT>

