<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hainan Sees `Steady Increase' in Tax Revenue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hainan Sees `Steady Increase' in Tax Revenue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK1204134794 Haikou Hainan People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1204134794 </F>
<F P=104>  Haikou Hainan People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Over the past two months since the new taxation 
system was introduced, Hainan's tax revenue has seen a steady 
increase. By the end of February, the province had collected 
486 million yuan in industrial and commercial taxes, 
representing an increase of 77.5 percent over the same period of 
the previous year, and completed 16.4 percent of the tasks 
assigned by the state, of which the central tax amounted to 119 
million yuan and the local tax stood at 366 million yuan. 
  Since the beginning of this year, in accordance with the 
requirements of the new taxation system and in light of the 
realities of the Hainan special zone's market economic structure 
and economic development, tax authorities at all levels in the 
province have done a good job of investigating tax funds and 
have delegated tax collection plans at all levels down to the 
tax collecting units. At the same time, they have persisted in 
managing taxation in accordance to the law and have strengthened 
tax collection and management, thus enabling the province to 
maintain a relatively good momentum of tax revenue growth. In 
terms of taxes, business tax, state-owned enterprises' income 
tax, and additional revenue from education fees saw 
comparatively large increases. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

