<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hunan Secretary, Governor at University Ceremony </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hunan Secretary, Governor at University Ceremony </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK1304013394 Changsha Hunan People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 2 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1304013394 </F>
<F P=104>  Changsha Hunan People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Hunan Agricultural University solemnly held 
a renaming ceremony and observed the 43th anniversary of its 
founding on 2 April. [passage omitted] Present at the 
ceremony were provincial party and government leaders, including 
Wang Maolin, Chen Bangzhu, Yang Zhengwu, Hu Biao, Wang Keying, 
and (Huang Daoqi), (Yang Zhangmin), and other veteran comrades. 
(Wen Hui), deputy secretary general of the provincial 
government, read out the State Education Commission's notice of 
endorsement on renaming the Hunan Agricultural College the Hunan 
Agricultural University. [passage omitted] 
  On behalf of the provincial government, Vice Governor Wang 
Keying delivered an ebullient speech. [passage omitted] 
  Amid warm applause Wang Maolin and Chen Bangzhu handed the 
nameplate of the Hunan Agricultural University to President 
(Peng Ganzhi). [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

