<F P=100> Northeast Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Harbin Sets Ceiling on Grain, Soybean Oil Prices </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Harbin Sets Ceiling on Grain, Soybean Oil Prices </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1104020794 Harbin Heilongjiang People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2200 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1104020794 </F>
<F P=104>  Harbin Heilongjiang People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Harbin city government decided to set a ceiling 
price for the marketing of grain and oil for a period of time. 
The ceiling prices will be effective today. 
  The specific standards for the ceiling prices are: The 
ceiling price for every five gram of first-grade soybean oil is 
3.7 yuan; that of first-grade rice, 0.84 yuan; and that of all 
sorts of flour, 0.79 yuan. 
  Harbin city government has called all state-owned, 
collective, and individual grain shops, and all enterprises 
doing business at the country trade fairs to resolutely 
implement the ceiling prices set for the aforementioned product 
varieties, put price tags on the products, and sell these 
products in line with the price tags. Those units that refuse to 
implement the ceiling prices, abritrarily raise the prices, and 
sell these products above the ceiling prices will be strictly 
handled in case they are discoverd. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

