<H3> <TI>   Wu Xueqian Meets ROK Parliament Speaker </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Wu Xueqian Meets ROK Parliament Speaker </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1204115594 Beijing XINHUA in English 1113 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1204115594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, April 12 (XINHUA) -- South Korean National 
Assembly Speaker Yi Man-sop today expressed appreciation for 
China's achievements made since the implementation of the 
open-door policy. 
  Yi made the statement when meeting with Wu Xueqian, 
vice-chairman of the Chinese People's Political Consultative 
Conference (PPCC). 
  Yi said China's success is attributable not only to the 
resolute determination of the Chinese Government to carry out 
the open-door policy but also to the support of the Chinese 
people. Yi visited China in January. 
  Both sides said they are satisfied with the development of 
bilateral relations since the diplomatic relations were 
established in August 1992. 
  They hold that fuller cooperation between the two sides will 
be conducive to mutual prosperity. 
  South Korea's ruling Democratic Liberal Party (DLP) Leader 
Kim Chong-pil will host a dinner in honor of Wu later today. 
  Wu arrived here Sunday for an eight-day goodwill visit at 
the 
invitation of Foreign Minister Han Sung-chu. 

</TEXT>

