<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Measures To Increase Agricultural Input Taken </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Measures To Increase Agricultural Input Taken </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1204072594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0614 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1204072594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 12 (XINHUA) -- The Chinese 
Government has taken a series of measures to increase its 
agricultural input in an effort to promote a sustained growth of 
farm production. 
  The central government has decided to add three billion yuan 
this year to its budget for capital construction, 650 million 
yuan of which will be put into farm production, accounting for 
21.7 percent of the total increase. 
  Also, loans offered by banks have risen by 19.8 billion yuan 
this year, 2.1 billion yuan destined for agriculture, accounting 
for 10.6 percent of the total added. 
  An analysis shows that the shrinkage of investment in 
agricultural capital construction is mainly due to the change of 
investment resources and the expansion of investment scale and 
scope. 
  To maintain a stable agricultural development, the central 
government has raised the budget and loans for farm production, 
12.9 percentage points more than last year. 
  In addition to the direct input into farming, forestry and 
water- conservancy works, the increased investment also covers 
the farm- support industries, including fertilizers, pesticides, 
plastic sheeting and farm machinery. 

</TEXT>

