<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hainan Popularizes Social Insurance System </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hainan Popularizes Social Insurance System </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1304120794 Beijing XINHUA in English 0948 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1304120794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Haikou, April 13 (XINHUA) -- The employees of all 
enterprises and institutions in Hainan Province, China's largest 
special economic zone, are now covered by a unified social 
insurance system. 
  In 1991, the Hainan Provincial Government issued preliminary 
guidelines for retirement, job injury, unemployment and medical 
insurance coverage. 
  The regulations have now been popularized, spreading from 
state-owned enterprises and some collectively-owned enterprises 
to all kinds of enterprises and institutions. 
  The province has standardized insurance rates as a 
proportion 
of total salary figures. 
  By the end of 1993, 9,298 enterprises, including 777 
foreign-funded ones, had joined the insurance service system. 
  About 732,000 employees will benefit from the services. 
  In 1993, 189,964 retired employees in Hainan received 
pensions and 681 unemployed workers received relief funds from 
the service. 
  At the end of last year, the Hainan Provincial People's 
Congress approved three sets of insurance regulations concerning 
retirement, job injury and unemployment. 
  The regulations have extended their scope to government 
organs and self-employed businesses. 
  Sources said that the insurance service system in Hainan has 
taken the lead in the development of the service in China. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

