<F P=100> Northeast Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Economic TV Station in Heilongjiang Established </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Economic TV Station in Heilongjiang Established </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1404040494 Harbin HEILONGJIANG RIBAO in Chinese 29 Mar 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> SK1404040494 </F>
<F P=104>  Harbin HEILONGJIANG RIBAO </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Wang Zengxiang (3769 1073 4382): "Heihe </F>
Economic Television Station Begins Broadcasting"] 
  [Text] The Heihe Economic Television 
Station--Heilongjiang's first economic television station 
officially approved by the state--began broadcasting on 28 March. 
  Heihe is one of China's first group of border cities opened 
to the outside world. Facing Russia's Blagoveshchensk across 
Heilong Jiang, it is China's largest border trade outlet. 
Aiming at promoting the economic and trade activities of China 
and Russia by establishing ties with the south and opening to 
the north, this television station carries programs, such as 
"Heihe Economic Information," "Golden Bridge," and "Collection 
of Border Trade Information," in Chinese and Russian languages 
beamed at Heihe and Blagoveshchensk every evening from Monday 
through Friday. The station applies enterprise management and 
hires personnel publicly. It is responsible for its own profits 
and deficits. 

</TEXT>

